{
  "texts": [
    "Though promising with an AP of 78.31% at the lower level, precision dropped to 31.05% at the higher barrier.",
    "Nevertheless, the limited resolution of climate data is inadequate for detecting variations in small climatic zones, such as India, which may experience cyclones of varying magnitudes (Dabhade et al. 2021).",
    "Single Image Super-Resolution (SISR) may be used to generate artificially enhanced High Resolution (HR) images, which can subsequently be employed to improve the accuracy of object detection systems (Park et al. 2003; Anwar et al. 2020; Liu et al. 2021).",
    "Dong et al.",
    "introduced the pioneer deep learning Convolutional Neural Network-based Super-Resolution (SRCNN) method."
  ]
}